Netiv HaGdud (Hebrew: נְתִיב הַגְּדוּד‎, lit. Path of the Battalion) is a moshav and Israeli settlement in the West Bank. Located in the Jordan Valley around twenty kilometres north of Jericho, it falls under the jurisdiction of Bik'at HaYarden Regional Council.. In 2016 it had a population of 190.
The international community considers Israeli settlements in the West Bank illegal under international law, but the Israeli government disputes this.
